  "datePublished": "2026-03-01",
  "description": "Rank is the comparative value position of a card within a suit or game-specific order in a card game. In a standard French-suited deck, the ranks are ace through king (thirteen per suit), but the relative ordering of those ranks varies by game. An ace may be the highest card, the lowest card, or both depending on context — in many poker variants, the ace ranks above a king in high hands but below a two in low straights.\n",
